definitions.definition: A drug smoked or ingested for euphoric effect, cannabis.
definitions.example: After smoking a bowl of that fine marijuana, they ate some brownies.

definitions.definition: The hemp plant itself, Cannabis sativa.
Food consumed before going to bed.
Any meal eaten in the evening; dinner eaten in the evening, rather than at noon.
A meal from a chip shop consisting of a deep-fried food with chips.
definitions.example: a fish supper; a pizza supper

definitions.definition: A drinker, especially one who drinks slowly (i.e., one who sups).
The tea plant (Camellia sinensis); a variety of this plant.
definitions.example: Darjeeling tea is grown in India.

definitions.definition: The dried leaves or buds of the tea plant; a variety of such leaves.
definitions.example: Go to the supermarket and buy some Darjeeling tea.

definitions.definition: The drink made by infusing these dried leaves or buds in hot water.
definitions.example: Would you like some tea?

definitions.definition: Any similar drink made by infusing parts of various other plants.
definitions.example: camomile tea; mint tea

definitions.definition: Meat stock served as a hot drink.
definitions.example: beef tea

definitions.definition: A cup or (East Asia) glass of any of these drinks, often with milk, sugar, lemon, and/or tapioca pearls.
A light midafternoon meal, typically but not necessarily including tea.
The break in play between the second and third sessions.
definitions.example: Australia were 490 for 7 at tea on the second day.

definitions.definition: Information, especially gossip.
definitions.example: Spill the tea on that drama, hon.

definitions.definition: To drink tea.
To take afternoon tea (the light meal).
A moment, a historical unit of time from China, about the amount of time needed to quickly drink a traditional cup of tea. It is now found in Chinese-language historical fiction.
A person employed to perform computations; one who computes.
(by restriction) A male computer, where the female computer is called a computress.

A programmable electronic device that performs mathematical calculations and logical operations, especially one that can process, store and retrieve large amounts of data very quickly; now especially, a small one for personal or home use employed for manipulating text or graphics, accessing the Internet, or playing games or media.
A collection of sheets of paper bound together to hinge at one edge, containing printed or written material, pictures, etc.
definitions.example: He was frustrated because he couldn't find anything about dinosaurs in the book.

definitions.definition: A long work fit for publication, typically prose, such as a novel or textbook, and typically published as such a bound collection of sheets, but now sometimes electronically as an e-book.
definitions.example: I have three copies of his first book.

definitions.definition: A major division of a long work.
definitions.example: Genesis is the first book of the Bible.

definitions.definition: A record of betting (from the use of a notebook to record what each person has bet).
definitions.example: I'm running a book on who is going to win the race.

definitions.definition: A convenient collection, in a form resembling a book, of small paper items for individual use.
definitions.example: a book of raffle tickets

definitions.definition: The script of a musical or opera.
(usually in the plural) Records of the accounts of a business.
A book award, a recognition for receiving the highest grade in a class (traditionally an actual book, but recently more likely a letter or certificate acknowledging the achievement).
(whist) Six tricks taken by one side.
Four of a kind
A document, held by the referee, of the incidents happened in the game.
(by extension) A list of all players who have been booked (received a warning) in a game.
The twenty-sixth Lenormand card.
Any source of instruction.
To reserve (something) for future use.
definitions.example: I can book tickets for the concert next week.

definitions.definition: To write down, to register or record in a book or as in a book.
definitions.example: They booked that message from the hill

definitions.definition: (law enforcement) To record the name and other details of a suspected offender and the offence for later judicial action.
definitions.example: The police booked him for driving too fast.

definitions.definition: To issue with a caution, usually a yellow card, or a red card if a yellow card has already been issued.
To travel very fast.
definitions.example: He was really booking, until he passed the speed trap.

definitions.definition: To record bets as bookmaker.
(law student slang) To receive the highest grade in a class.
definitions.example: The top three students had a bet on which one was going to book their intellectual property class.

definitions.definition: To leave.
definitions.example: He was here earlier, but he booked.

definitions.definition: (with person as subject) To cook (something) in an oven.
definitions.example: I baked a delicious cherry pie.

definitions.definition: (with baked thing as subject) To be cooked in an oven.
definitions.example: The cake baked at 350°F.

definitions.definition: To be warmed to drying and hardening.
definitions.example: The clay baked in the sun.

definitions.definition: To dry by heat.
definitions.example: They baked the electrical parts lightly to remove moisture.

definitions.definition: To be hot.
definitions.example: I'm baking after that workout in the gym.

definitions.definition: To cause to be hot.
To smoke marijuana.
To harden by cold.
To fix (lighting, reflections, etc.) as part of the texture of an object to improve rendering performance.
(with "in" or "into") To incorporate into something greater.
